text: Shahsavaran (, also Romanized as Shāhsavārān; also known as Shāhsavār) is a village in Moshkabad Rural District, in the Central District of Arak County, Markazi Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 864, in 254 families. == References == Category:Populated places in Arak County
title: Shahsavaran
